              "pubDate": "Thu, 25 Jun 2026 22:28:28 GMT",
              "description": "Sí, se puede – yes, we can – was the chant that rang out from the 55,000 Ecuador fans as their team’s final group match kicked off. Despite a flat start to their World Cup campaign, there was a genuine belief that an upset against a full-strength Germany was possible. They had no other choice: having been shut out by Eloy Room’s heroics for Curaçao , Sebastián Beccacece’s side had to win to progress. This time, a stirring performance earned La Tri a famous victory against an error-prone Mannschaft . Gonzalo Plata’s 77th-minute strike sparked wild and emotional celebrations, assuring their place in the last 32 as one of the eight best third-placed team. Continue reading...",
